{"questionId":"17790","questionHtml":"<p>The Feynman diagram shows some of the changes in a proton–proton collision.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/6958d46cb41403df0f17a47e022d56e5a7f17366.png\" width=\"360\" height=\"423\">What is the equation for this collision?</p>\n<p>A.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">p</mi><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">p</mi><mo>→</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">p</mi><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mo>+</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">p</mi><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">p</mi><mo>→</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">p</mi><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mo>+</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mo>-</mo></msup></math></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">p</mi><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">p</mi><mo>→</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">p</mi><mo>+</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mo>¯</mo></mover><mo>+</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">p</mi><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">p</mi><mo>→</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">p</mi><mo>+</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mo>¯</mo></mover><mo>+</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mo>-</mo></msup></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>A</p>","meta":{"questionId":"17790","referenceCode":"20N.1.SL.TZ0.30","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"The Feynman diagram shows some of the changes in a proton–proton collision. What is the equation for this collision? A. p+p→p+n+π+ B. p+p→p+n+π- C. p+p→p+n¯+π+ D. p+p→p+n¯+π-","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"30","marksAvailable"